+./sdp/verification/t-009@20260425t183959z-verify.md:11:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-25T22:03:04.365Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-009@20260425T183959Z\n\n**Task:** Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`.\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-009@20260425t183959z-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-009@20260425T183959Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
+./sdp/verification/t-009@20260425t183959z-verify.md:50:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-25T22:03:41.483Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777154621483_0","parameters":{"content":"\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport numpy as np\nimport wave\nimport sqlite3\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add the tools directory to path\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \"my-claw\", \"tools\"))\nfrom sample_capture_daemon import save_capture\n\ndef verify_capture():\n    test_root = Path(\"temp_test_capture\")\n    if test_root.exists():\n        import shutil\n        shutil.rmtree(test_root)\n    test_root.mkdir()\n\n    sample_rate = 48000\n    # 1 second of 440Hz tone at -20dBFS\n    t = np.arange(sample_rate) / sample_rate\n    samples = (0.1 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * 440.0 * t)).astype(np.float32)\n\n    capture = save_capture(\n        samples,\n        source=\"room\",\n        sample_rate=sample_rate,\n        capture_root=test_root,\n        context={\"organism\": {\"arc_phase\": \"test\"}},\n        captured_at=1777152600.0  # 2026-04-25T21:30:00Z\n    )\n\n    print(f\"Captured to: {capture.path}\")\n    print(f\"Gain applied: {capture.gain_db} dB\")\n\n    # Verify WAV properties\n    with wave.open(str(capture.path), \"rb\") as f:\n        print(f\"Channels: {f.getnchannels()}\")\n        print(f\"Sample width: {f.getsampwidth()}\")\n        print(f\"Framerate: {f.getframerate()}\")\n        assert f.getnchannels() == 1\n        assert f.getsampwidth() == 3  # 24-bit\n        assert f.getframerate() == 48000\n\n    # Verify filename\n    filename = capture.path.name\n    print(f\"Filename: {filename}\")\n    assert filename.startswith(\"room_20260425T213000Z_test_\")\n    assert filename.endswith(\".wav\")\n\n    # Verify DB\n    index_path = test_root / \"index.sqlite\"\n    assert index_path.exists()\n    with sqlite3.connect(str(index_path)) as con:\n        row = con.execute(\"SELECT source, gain_db FROM samples WHERE sample_id = ?\", (capture.sample_id,)).fetchone()\n        print(f\"DB Row: {row}\")\n        assert row[0] == \"room\"\n        assert abs(row[1] - capture.gain_db) < 1e-6\n\n    print(\"Manual verification SUCCESS\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    verify_capture()\n","file_path":"manual_verify_t009.py"}}
