+# Verification Report — T-019 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260425T183959Z_1777164786.log
+
+**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI
+**Date:** 2026-04-26
+**Artifacts Reviewed:**
+- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py`
+- `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`
+- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/harmonic_planner.py`
+- `ESCALATIONS.md`
+
+## Correctness
+The implementation of `transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> int` correctly computes the smallest semitone offset required to align a sample's detected pitch with the nearest in-key pitch class. It handles the octave wrap correctly by searching in both directions. The tie-breaking logic favors negative transposition, which is consistent and verified by tests.
+
+## Completeness
+All acceptance criteria are met:
+- Transposition maps `pitch_hz` to the nearest in-key pitch using the artist's B-rooted palette.
+- Samples with `pitch_confidence < 0.4` or `pitch_hz <= 0` return 0 semitones, correctly playing "atonally".
+- Tests cover known pitch/key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and octave wrap shortest-path selection.
+
+## Consistency
+The implementation leverages `harmonic_planner.py` for canonical key normalization and scale definitions, ensuring consistency with the rest of the SenseWeave harmony engine. The coding style and test patterns match the existing codebase.
+
+## Security
+No security vulnerabilities were identified. The implementation uses standard math libraries and does not involve unsafe operations or credential handling.
+
+## Quality
+The code is concise, well-documented, and follows idiomatic Python patterns. The tests are comprehensive and use appropriate fixtures (standard within the project). Mandatory hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were found to be already addressed in the daemon startup flows (`daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`).
+
+## Issues Found
+- [x] (Minor/Environmental) `pytest tests/ -x` encountered a `PermissionError` in `test_daemon_fallback.py` due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions on `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`. This is an environmental constraint unrelated to the T-019 changes. Focused tests for the new implementation (`tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py`) passed successfully.
+
+## Verdict: PASS
+
+## Notes for Lead Agent
+The implementation is solid and integrates well with the established harmonic planning utilities. No further actions required for this task.
