sdp/verification/t-019 @20260425t183959z-verify.md:12:The implementation of `transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> int` correctly computes the smallest semitone offset required to align a sample's detected pitch with the nearest in-key pitch class. It handles the octave wrap correctly by searching in both directions. The tie-breaking logic favors negative transposition, which is consistent and verified by tests.
sdp/logs/Verify_T-019_20260425T183959Z_1777164786.log:10:- `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays "atonally" as a texture<br/>- tests verify transposition for known pitch + key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and edge cases (octave wraps)
