ats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\\n-| 39 | T-039 | Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. | T2 | 4 | 6 | CCH-038 | — | - offline renderer produces 5-minute proxy audio for fixture pieces<br/>- librosa self-similarity matrix + Foote novelty curve extracted<br/>- symbolic novelty peaks (from CCH-034) must align with audio novelty peaks within ±500 ms<br/>- catches cases where symbolic metrics look fine but synthesis flattens expression |\\n-| 40 | T-040 | Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. | T2 | 5 | 6 | CCH-040 | — | - `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` describes cadence, how to ablate a rule, how to attach a review note<br/>- weekly review log at `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` with template entries (piece, date, felt-wrong symptom, suspected rule, ablation result, action)<br/>- tests: doc and template exist and link to the ablation CLI from CCH-010 |\\n+| 33 | T-033 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. | T2 | 3 | 6 | CCS-032 | — | - `tools/sample_library_import.py` script reads a TOML manifest of source files + intended tags and inserts them into the library<br/>- supports both single-file and directory imports<br/>- preserves provenance (original path, captured-by) in `SampleRecord` extras<br/>- 100+ samples land in the library with accurate tags<br/>- tests cover the importer with a small fixture manifest |\\n \\n-**Sprint 6 total:** ~18 hrs\\n+**Sprint 6 total:** ~6 hrs\\n \\n ---\\n \\n ## Summary\\n \\n - **Sprint 1 (Versioning System):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\\n-- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 8 tasks, ~24 hrs\\n-- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\\n+- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 3 tasks, ~12 hrs\\n+- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening)