ss unchanged<br/>- existing `test_artist_identity.py::TestSignatureVoices::test_quartet_size` is renamed to `test_quintet_size` and asserts length 5; quartet-specific assertions migrated |\n+| 30 | T-030 | Add `sampler_density` field (0.0–1.0) to `ArtistMode` with mode-specific values: solitary 0.7, companion 0.25, working_ambience 0.10, evening_reflection 0.65, storm 0.45. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-007 | T-001 | - `ArtistMode` dataclass gains `sampler_density: float = 0.25` with documentation<br/>- existing five modes updated to the values above<br/>- `apply_mode_to_commission` propagates `sampler_density` into `mode_sampler_density` metadata<br/>- tests verify each mode's value, propagation, and that `sampler_density` is bounded [0.0, 1.0] |\n+| 31 | T-031 | Register `voice_sampler` character in `character_registry.py` with `voice.synth = \"sw_sampler\"`, `voice.role = \"sampler\"`, default register, and per-mode gain overrides. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-008 | T-001 | - `character_registry.py` gains `voice_sampler` entry with synth=`sw_sampler`, role=`sampler`, register=`[36, 84]`, params containing default grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose<br/>- character is selectable by `select_cast_ids` when `preferred_synths` includes `sw_sampler`<br/>- tests verify registration and selection through cast planner |\n+| 32 | T-032 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-009 | T-001 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |\n \n **Sprint 5 total:** ~27 hrs\n \n@@ -83,20 +78,18 @@\n \n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\n-| 38 | T-038 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | T2 | 3 | 6 | CCH-032 | — | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\n-| 39 | T-039 | Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. | T2 | 4 | 6 | CCH-038 | — | - offline renderer produces 5-minute proxy audio for fixture pieces<br/>- librosa self-similarity matrix + Foote novelty curve extracted<br/>- symbolic novelty peaks (from CCH-034) must align with audio novelty peaks within ±500 ms<br/>- catches cases where symbolic metrics look fine but synthesis flattens expression |\n-| 40 | T-040 | Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. | T2 | 5 | 6 | CCH-040 | — | - `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` describes cadence, how to ablate a rule, how to attach a review note<br/>- weekly review log at `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` with template entries (piece, date, felt-wrong symptom, suspected rule, ablation result, action)<br/>- tests: doc and template exist and link to the ablation CLI from CCH-010 |\n+| 33 | T-033 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field record