sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Zc_1777158076.log:2361:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:113:| CCS-025 | Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays "atonally" as a texture<br/>- tests verify transposition for known pitch + key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and edge cases (octave wraps) |
