ngs into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. | T2 | 3 | 6 | CCS-032 | — | - `tools/sample_library_import.py` script reads a TOML manifest of source files + intended tags and inserts them into the library<br/>- supports both single-file and directory imports<br/>- preserves provenance (original path, captured-by) in `SampleRecord` extras<br/>- 100+ samples land in the library with accurate tags<br/>- tests cover the importer with a small fixture manifest |\n \n-**Sprint 6 total:** ~18 hrs\n+**Sprint 6 total:** ~6 hrs\n \n ---\n \n ## Summary\n \n - **Sprint 1 (Versioning System):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\n-- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 8 tasks, ~24 hrs\n-- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening):** 10 tasks, ~30 hrs\n+- **Sprint 2 (Quality Scoring):** 3 tasks, ~12 hrs\n+- **Sprint 3 (Improvement Engine Hardening):** 10 tasks, ~36 hrs\n - **Sprint 5 (Library & CRUD Polish):** 9 tasks, ~27 hrs\n-- **Sprint 6 (Stretch Goals):** 3 tasks, ~18 hrs\n+- **Sprint 6 (Stretch Goals):** 1 tasks, ~6 hrs\n \n-**Total: 40 tasks, ~129 hours**\n+**Total: 33 tasks, ~111 hours**"}
sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260425T183959Zd_1777146814.log:658:./sdp/prd-snapshot.md:119:| CCS-025 | Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays "atonally" as a texture<br/>- tests verify transposition for known pitch + key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and edge cases (octave wraps) |
