## Correctness
`sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name)` is implemented and returns an integer semitone offset, with low-confidence and zero/invalid pitch guards returning `0`. The implementation computes pitch class with A4-based midi mapping, maps to key/root scale degrees via `harmonic_planner`, and returns the nearest in-key pitch class offset.

## Completeness
The acceptance checklist items are covered in unit tests:
- Known pitch/key combinations are tested (e.g., B minor, C major, C5 wrap, octave reuse).
- Low-confidence behavior returns zero transposition (`0.39 < 0.4` path).
- Edge cases are included for wrap-around and zero pitch.

